description:
DKT, das kauf&auml;mnnische Talent, is an Austrian pendant for the well-known Monopoly. This version is very similar to &raquo;DKT dynamic&laquo;, but it has some party-elements.
As in DKT dynamic the goal is to pay back the starting money. The prices of the alpine regions change with the seasons. On two fields, all the players have to perform a task (depending on the season). The last one has to pay &hellip;

Hier wird in den alpinen Tourismus investiert. Die Spieler erstehen Grundst&uuml;cke in den Alpen und versuchen sie durch den Ausbau mit H&uuml;tten und Hotels lukrativ zu machen, ihr Geld zu mehren und schuldenfrei zu werden. Sommer- und Wintertourismus erfordern unterschiedliche Aktivit&auml;ten und Touristenattraktionen.

Faggles to Faggles -- an outrageous, queered-up party game for you to enjoy with the girls.  In this game of judging (hey, it's what gays do best), each card is more outrageous than the next.

Here's the deal: grab three friends or more and then draw a card with an adjective on it. The rest of the players, who hold cards with nouns on them, must play the card they think you would choose for that adjective. So, if you drew the card &ldquo;racist&rdquo; would you pick &ldquo;the French,&rdquo; &ldquo;Miss Piggy&rdquo; or &ldquo;rainbows?&rdquo;

Each card has a unique, hilarious definition that will keep you in stitches time and time again. A small investment of fifty bucks will get you hours and hours and hours and hours of entertainment.  Believe us, we've played this game with dozens of people for hundreds of hours and it never gets old.

Objective: be the first to get the permanent majority of votes for the coming election of the mayor - learn more about the city of Quedlinburg
 - simple 'Roll and Move' game, very similar to Monopoly , moving by turn -
Each player rolls the die, moves according the number, follows instruction of space landed on, buys - if possible and/or preferable - votes ;
that's more or less the only difference compared with Monopoly;
"chance" cards are created with circumstances out of the history of Quedlinburg

Objective: be the first travelling through 6 continents & becoming the 'Voxtours-Champion'
 - acting by turn -
each player picks up his passport jetting through a continents;
3 questions must be asked properly before getting a new visa;
questions to be solved may challenge your knowledge about language, sight seeings, local delicacies, flora & fauna, currencies, airports....
Only a new visa will allow you to travel to the next continent.

Objective: be the first catching the fox before fox has finished
the circuit
 - moving by turn/'Roll & Move' game -
each player starts from the alpine hut, fox (red meeple) with 5-10 spaces ahead; fox must reach top of the mountain (Kahleberg) and return successfully to alpine hut;
players should arrange themselves which route is followed by whom;
fox can't run past a hunter (but turn) and is caught if hunter's roll ends on the same space

Objective: gain as many of the 44 Micky cards as possible
 - moving/acting by turn -
each player moves according the die into a free of coice direction; ending on a marked/coloured space draw a question card;
name - according colour - a land (green); a town (red), a river/lake (blue), a mountain (brown) starting with the letter printed on card; if you are quick enough keep the card; 
ending on a 'Mickymouse' symbol draw a 'term' card to determine the colour, hereafter a question card; proceed like described above - but if you are successful you'll get a 2nd chance to win an additional card

Objective: be the first bringing all of your 3 spaceships back to Earth
 - simple 'Roll & Move' game -
each player gets 3 spaceships;
roll the die and follow the red line to mars unless you end up on a space forcing you to change the route;
you may follow the green line back to earth only if all of your spaceships are landed successfully on mars - same approach compared to outward flight
